# Stand-up Visualisation Backend

A simple Express Web API for the storage and serving of data from SOON_'s daily morning stand-ups.

# Group Staff Members

Resources related to Staff Members in the API.

## Staff Members Collection [/staff-members]

### List All Staff Members [GET]

+ Request (application/json; charset=utf-8)

    + Headers

            Accept: application/json

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "_embedded": {
                "staffMembers": [
                    {
                        "ID": "bf4b3b30-792c-11e7-9e1d-b10f7e8a2b0a",
                        "firstName": "foo",
                        "lastName": "bar",
                        "fullName": "foo bar",
                        "role": "developer",
                        "_links": {
                            "self": {
                                "href": "/v1/staff-members/bf4b3b30-792c-11e7-9e1d-b10f7e8a2b0a"
                            }
                        }
                    }
                ]
            },
            "_links":{
                "self": {
                    "href": "/staff-members"
                }
            }
        }

### Create a Staff Member [POST]

You may create a new Staff Member with this action. It takes a JSON object
containing a role and name information about the new Member.

+ firstName (string)
+ lastName (string)
+ role (string) - For example Designer, Developer or Producer.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "firstName": "Foo",
            "lastName": "Bar",
            "role": "Foo"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "ID": "bf4b3b30-792c-11e7-9e1d-b10f7e8a2b0a",
                "firstName": "foo",
                "lastName": "bar",
                "fullName": "foo bar",
                "role": "developer",
                "_links": {
                    "self": {
                        "href": "/v1/staff-members/bf4b3b30-792c-11e7-9e1d-b10f7e8a2b0a"
                    }
                }
            }

## Staff Member [/staff-members/{id}]

